explanation: Maintain a sorted vector of disjoint intervals. addRange merges overlapping/adjacent intervals in one linear pass and re-sorts. queryRange uses binary search to check containment. removeRange splits or discards intervals as needed. Vector operations are cache-friendly and avoid pointer overhead, giving good practical performance for 10^4 calls.

